Road accidents not only lead to fatalities but also drive families into poverty as victims are often breadwinners, according to Richard Scurfield of the World Bank.
China faces a grim prediction of half a million deaths annually by 2020 unless immediate action is taken.
Factors like speeding and drunken driving contribute to the high death rate.
In Argentina, a crackdown on seat belt violations has motorists reluctantly buckling up.
Meanwhile, in Uganda, strict traffic regulations are being enforced, with fines for passengers not wearing seat belts.
ASEAN countries are also taking steps to enhance road safety and reduce casualties through various measures.
